def _unstack_multiple(data, clocs, fill_value=None):
    if len(clocs) == 0:
        return data

    index = data.index

    clocs = [index._get_level_number(i) for i in clocs]

    rlocs = [i for i in range(index.nlevels) if i not in clocs]

    if rlocs == []:
        # Everything is in clocs, so the dummy df has a regular index
        dummy_index = pd.RangeIndex(len(data))
    else:
        # Create a new MultiIndex for the dummy index
        levels = [index.levels[i] for i in rlocs] + [range(len(data))]
        codes = [index.codes[i] for i in rlocs] + [np.repeat(range(len(data)), len(index.levels[0]))]
        dummy_index = pd.MultiIndex(levels=levels, codes=codes)

    dummy = data.copy()
    dummy.index = dummy_index

    unstacked = dummy.unstack(clocs, fill_value=fill_value)

    return unstacked
